If your project is large enough to maintain docs they would be here.

This project is small so its docs are contained in the readme.rst

You can read more about documentation here: http://sphinx-doc.org/

For structuring python project, see these links:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RKHMnevITF0&t=297s
https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/python-virtual-environment/

For Virtual environment, see these links:

https://stackoverflow.com/questions/13206990/virtualenv-env-not-creating-bin-directory-in-windows-7
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/56973291/how-to-fix-seemingly-endless-loop-while-creating-virtual-environment-with-python

To install the package from your local machine globally,
python -m pip install -e D:\machine_learning_utility

To install the package from your local machine into the same directory,
pip install .

To create .pypirc file,
https://docs.python.org/3.2/distutils/packageindex.html

For deployment to PyPi,
https://packaging.python.org/tutorials/packaging-projects/

For installing a package,
https://packaging.python.org/tutorials/installing-packages/